items.title: Lindor joins elite company with 30th home run
items.summary: Francisco Lindor insists that he is not a power hitter. As the Indians' shortstop tore around the bases on Tuesday night, in front of a Progressive Field audience that shook the ballpark in celebration, Lindor continued to play the role of the unlikely slugger well.

items.title: With Hamilton down, Reds reinstate Winker
items.summary: Jesse Winker, the Reds' No. 5 prospect, was reinstated from the disabled list before Tuesday's game against the Cardinals. He got the start in right field and hit leadoff.
